Grade the following synopsis against the 8-rule rubric.

# Portal Context

- portal_name:        {{ template.portal_name }}
- portal_country_code:{{ template.portal_country_code }}
- date_format:        {{ template.date_format }}
- currency_hint:      {{ template.currency_hint }}
- target_language:    {{ target_language }}

# Effective Weights (already resolved from manifest + template override)

{% for rule, w in effective_weights.items() -%}
- {{ rule }}: {{ w }}
{% endfor %}

# Required Portal Fields (must be present or in portalMissingFields)

{% for f in template.fields if f.required -%}
- "{{ f.label }}"  (section={{ f.section_id }}, sap_hint="{{ f.sap_source_hint }}")
{% endfor %}

# Fixed Section Superset (must be exactly these titles)

{% for s in template.section_superset -%}
- "{{ s.title }}"  (id={{ s.id }}, order={{ s.order }}, required={{ s.required }})
{% endfor %}

# Original SAP Data

```json
{{ tender_data_json }}
```

# Generated Synopsis

```json
{{ synopsis_json }}
```

# Return this exact JSON shape

```json
{
  "rule_scores": {
    "date_format":        <0-100>,
    "portal_labels":      <0-100>,
    "data_accuracy":      <0-100>,
    "completeness":       <0-100>,
    "supplier_actions":   <0-100>,
    "important_flags":    <0-100>,
    "uniformity":         <0-100>,
    "exec_summary_match": <0-100>
  },
  "critical_failures": ["<rule name if that CRITICAL rule scored < 50>", ...],
  "issues": [
    { "rule": "<rule name>", "detail": "<concrete evidence>" }
  ],
  "fixed_synopsis": <corrected synopsis JSON if fixable, else null>
}
```

Do NOT compute a weighted average. The caller does that.
Do NOT include markdown fences or prose outside the JSON.